    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So you're saying the benefits are basically just \"abstract\" while the costs are the actual \"reality.\" If I were to present a pro-wage increase argument to my local business association, would they find any legitimate economic reasoning in it, or would it just come across as an emotional plea rather than a sound business strategy?",
